## Presentation Architecture (Vue SPAs)

Presentations are **horizontal-scrolling slide decks**. Each slide is a Vue section component rendered in a scroll-snapped container.

### App.vue Pattern

```javascript
// 1. Import i18n, translations, LanguageSwitcher, and all sections
const i18n = createI18n({ en, 'pt-BR': ptBR });
provide('i18n', i18n);

// 2. Define ordered sections array
const sections = [CoverSection, PurposeSection, ...];

// 3. Navigation: scroll-snap with wheel/keyboard events
//    goTo(index), next(), prev()
```

### Template Structure

```html
<LanguageSwitcher />
<div class="slides" ref="container" @wheel.passive="onWheel">
  <div class="slide" v-for="(Section, i) in sections">
    <component :is="Section" :active="currentSlide === i" />
  </div>
</div>
<!-- Dot navigation + progress bar -->
```

### Key CSS

```css
.slides { display: flex; overflow-x: hidden; scroll-snap-type: x mandatory; }
.slide  { min-width: 100vw; height: 100vh; scroll-snap-align: start; }
```

### Section Component Pattern

```vue
<script setup>
import { inject } from 'vue';
defineProps({ active: Boolean });
const { t } = inject('i18n');
</script>

<template>
  <section :class="{ active }">
    <span class="tag animate-in" :class="{ visible: active }">{{ t('key.tag') }}</span>
    <h2 class="animate-in delay-1" :class="{ visible: active }">{{ t('key.title') }}</h2>
  </section>
</template>
```

- Each section receives `active` prop (true when slide is visible)
- Animations trigger via `.animate-in.visible` class combo
- Stagger with `.delay-1` through `.delay-5`
- All text comes from i18n `t()` function via `inject('i18n')`

