## Internationalization (i18n)

Two locales: **EN** (default) and **PT-BR**. See `language-switcher.mdc` for full implementation details.

### Vue Context

- Composable: `packages/theme-nexuslabz/composables/useI18n.js`
- Translation files: `presentations/{name}/src/i18n/en.js` and `pt-BR.js`
- Provided via `provide('i18n', ...)`, consumed via `inject('i18n')`
- Component: `packages/theme-nexuslabz/components/LanguageSwitcher.vue`

### Static HTML Context

- Uses `data-en` and `data-pt` attributes on elements
- Vanilla JS swaps `innerHTML` based on locale
- Locale persisted in `localStorage` key `nexus-locale`
- Language switcher uses identical BEM classes: `lang-dd`, `lang-dd__trigger`, etc.

